      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DIVINE GIRL (6) has been most impressive of late and made it two wins in a row when she led from one spot wider than this at her latest appearance and kept going to score by 6 metres. That took her strike rate at this circuit and distance to 50 per cent. Can land the hat trick. WHERES THE GOLD NZ (5) disappointed last start at Penrith but did have to work from a back row draw. Led from a similar draw for fourth in a stronger race here prior. His best form would see him hard to stop. PAS DE CHEVAL (3) had a tough draw last time but is much better served here and has claims off the placing two back. LAYLA SHANNON (1) should get the favours from the ace draw and has been racing well from wider barriers with a win and a placing in her last two attempts at this circuit and distance.",
